- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Subspace clustering is often used in computer vision applications, such as image segmentation and object recognition. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): Clustering algorithms involve mathematical concepts such as distance metrics and optimization functions. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Clustering can also be applied to network analysis, such as identifying communities in social networks. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): Clustering can also be applied to natural language processing tasks, such as topic modeling and document clustering.
